ActBoards of Trade Act
SubjectOrder Approving the Boundary Change of the Chambre de commerce de Montréal Centre Sud Ouest/The Montreal Center South West Chamber of Commerce
PrecisOrder approving the application by the CHAMBRE DE COMMERCE DE MONTRÉAL CENTRE SUD OUEST/THE MONTREAL CENTER SOUTH WEST CHAMBER OF COMMERCE, in Quebec, to CHANGE THE BOUNDARIES of its district from the boroughs of LaSalle, Verdun, Sud-Ouest, Côte-des-Neiges–Notre-Dame-de-Grâce, the portion of the Ville-Marie borough located west of Saint-Laurent Boulevard, including the King Edward Quay, the Alexandra Quay, the Bickerdike Quay and the Cité du Havre, the portion of the borough of Lachine/Saint-Pierre lying east of the St-Pierre interchange, north of the Lachine Canal and north-east of Highway 20, being the territory of the former City of Saint-Pierre, the portion of the Plateau-Mont-Royal borough lying between Sherbrooke Street to the south, Mont-Royal Avenue to the north, Saint-Laurent Boulevard to the east, and Parc and University streets to the west, the cities of Westmount, Côte-Saint-Luc, Montreal West and Hampstead to the boroughs of LaSalle, Verdun, Sud-Ouest, Outremont, Côte-des-Neiges–Notre-Dame-de-Grâce, the portion of the Ville-Marie borough located west of Saint-Laurent Boulevard, including the King Edward Quay, the Alexandra Quay, the Bickerdike Quay and the Cité du Havre, the portion of the borough of Lachine/Saint-Pierre lying east of the St-Pierre interchange, north of the Lachine Canal and north-east of Highway 20, being the territory of the former City of Saint-Pierre, the portion of the Plateau-Mont-Royal borough lying between Sherbrooke Street to the south and Saint-Laurent Boulevard to the east, the cities of Westmount, Côte-Saint-Luc, Montreal West, and Hampstead.
